Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.15,0:49:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}總統先生收
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.70,0:00:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們的總統不僅服用精神藥物\NWe have a president who not only took mind-altering medication --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.89,0:00:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當美國艦隊與中國對峙時\Na man who has his finger on the button
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.18,0:00:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可以隨時批准實施打擊\Nwhile U.S. Ships are squaring off with China --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還授意他的白宮顧問去干預...\Nbut then instructed his White House counsel to coach a --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.78,0:00:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,據稱  先生  沒有被證實\NAllegedly, sir. Not proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.61,0:00:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去干預證人  他的做法\NTo coach a witness. Which is behavior either resulting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.92,0:00:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要麼是受藥物影響  要麼更糟\Nfrom the use of those drugs, or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.52,0:00:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是有意想踐踏法律\Na deliberate attempt to obstruct the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.78,0:00:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不覺得兩種情況都該被彈劾嗎\NNow wouldn't you call either scenario impeachable?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.74,0:00:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那該由國會決定  先生  而不是我\NThat's for the United States Congress to decide, sir. Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.31,0:00:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道總統在服用任何藥物嗎\NWere you aware that the president was taking any form of medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.34,0:00:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我不知道\NNo, I was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.62,0:00:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你注意到他舉止古怪嗎\NDid you notice him acting in a bizarre fashion?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-情緒不穩  語無倫次  -沒有  先生\N- Unstable, incoherent? - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.91,0:00:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有任何奇怪的行為嗎  -沒有  先生\N- Any odd behavior? - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.25,0:00:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在貿易戰之際解雇幕僚長不算嗎\NNot even firing his chief of staff in the midst of a trade war?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他沒有解雇我  是我主動辭職的\NHe didn't fire me. I resigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.02,0:00:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能告訴我們為什麼嗎\NWould you tell us why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.37,0:00:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我辭職是因為我覺得自己無法\NI resigned because I felt I could no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.39,0:00:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再以最好的狀態為總統服務\Nserve the president to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,發生了什麼變化  是什麼讓你得出那樣的結論\NAnd what changed? How did you come to that conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.15,0:01:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我與白宮中的某些人\NI had some fundamental differences of opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.24,0:01:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本理念不合\Nwith certain people in the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.31,0:01:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如誰  總統嗎\NLike who? The president?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.63,0:01:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  先生\NNo, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那某些人是指誰\NWell, what certain people then?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,實際上只有一個人\NOne person, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.61,0:01:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統  弗蘭克·安德伍德\NThe vice president, Frank Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.04,0:01:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想讓你離開嗎\NHe wanted you gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.87,0:01:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不敢說副總統想怎麼樣  不想怎麼樣\NI can't speak as to what the vice president did or didn't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.95,0:01:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想要隱藏什麼嗎\NWas he trying to hide anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.76,0:01:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是不是怕你曝光什麼\NWas he afraid you might expose something?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.43,0:01:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你得去問他  先生\NYou'd have to ask him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.25,0:01:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法委員會正在上演的是一齣鬧劇\NWhat's happening in the Judiciary Committee is a farce.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.11,0:01:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和黨正在利用這種...\NThe Republicans are exploiting the situ--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.84,0:01:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,插一句  副總統先生\NExcuse me, Mr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.89,0:01:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不僅僅是共和黨\Nbut it's not just Republicans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不少民主黨人也站出來說\NA number of Democrats have come out saying
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們支持彈劾\Nthey would support impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.47,0:01:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,包括多數黨黨鞭  傑姬·夏普\NIncluding the Majority Whip, Jackie Sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.76,0:01:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這令人髮指\NWhich is egregious,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.20,0:01:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為委員會還在進行聽證\Nsince the committee hasn't stopped hearing testimony,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.41,0:01:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特別檢察官也沒有完成調查\Nand nor has the special prosecutor completed her investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.48,0:01:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你極力維護總統\NYou vigorously defend the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有報道稱你們已經鬧僵\Nbut there are reports that you've had a falling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們好幾個星期沒說過話了\NThat you haven't spoken in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.61,0:01:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一派胡言\NThat is simply not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我與白宮的高級官員通過話\NI've spoken to senior staff at the White House
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.66,0:02:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說總統擔心你會在2016年大選中與他競爭\Nwho say the president is worried you want to run against him in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而就在今天  琳達·瓦斯奎茲暗指你...\NAnd just today Linda Vasquez intimated that you --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.61,0:02:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信總統一定會在2016年競選連任\NLook, I fully expect that the president will run in 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且我希望他能夠慷慨地邀請我\Nand I hope he's generous enough to invite me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作他的競選夥伴\Nto be his running mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.39,0:02:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彈劾  定罪  如果是這個結果呢\NImpeachment, conviction. Let's say it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.05,0:02:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會的  他完全是無辜的\NIt won't. He's completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們假設一下  你成了總統\NLet's say it does happen. You become president.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.14,0:02:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不會去想像那個情形\NThat is not a scenario I'm going to entertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.05,0:02:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你腦中肯定有過這個想法\NBut the thought must have crossed your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且可以說  如果不是因為你\NAnd one could make the argument that the president
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.79,0:02:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統也不會陷入這樣的窘境\Nwouldn't be in this predicament if it weren't for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.95,0:02:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你的幕僚長與馮和拉尼根的牽連\NIt's your staff's involvement with Feng and Lanagin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.95,0:02:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才引發了鄧巴的調查\Nthat expanded Dunbar's investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-隨之發現了出行記錄  -這些彈劾聽證\N- which resulted in the travel logs - Look, these impeachment hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.39,0:02:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是政治操縱的結果\Nare the result of political maneuvering,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-而不是  -是你在操縱還是共和黨\N- not the fact that-- - Your maneuverings, or the Republicans?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.53,0:02:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莫裏  我一直很喜歡你  你的問題很尖銳\NMorley, I've always liked you. You ask the tough questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.02,0:02:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你當然可以質疑我的判斷\NAnd you can certainly question my judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.37,0:02:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不要質疑我的愛國心\NBut do not question my patriotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我為國家和總統服務  而不是我自己\NI serve this nation and my president, not myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:02:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他滿口謊言\NHe's lying through his teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.04,0:02:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們所做的已經見效了\NWhat we're doing is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓大家一直私下談論\NWe keep the whisper campaign alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.10,0:03:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們讓他顯得渴望權利  顯得奸詐\NWe spin him as power-hungry, as duplicitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.77,0:03:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將焦點集中在他身上  而不是您\NFocus attention on him. Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最新支持率是多少  20%嗎\NWhat's the latest? 20%?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佐格比的數據是24%  您的講話起了作用\NZogby has you at 24. Your speech made a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.53,0:03:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支持率正在上升\NThe approval numbers are moving in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.06,0:03:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能再這麼小打小鬧了\NWe need to do more than play the spin game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們要打垮弗蘭克  讓他而不是我去當犧牲品\NWe need to destroy Frank. Offer his head instead of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我們利用雷蒙德·塔斯克  -怎麼利用\N- We use Raymond Tusk. - How?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.98,0:03:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他的聽證會上  在他去司法委員會時\NAt his hearing. When he goes to the Judiciary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.46,0:03:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  您已經被指控干預一個證人了\NSir, you're already being accused of coaching one witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果您再干預另一...\NIf you take steps to coach anoth--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是干預  是讓他說出事實\NNot coaching. The truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.25,0:03:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德承認洗錢\NRaymond admits to the money laundering,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.96,0:03:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把弗蘭克推到風口浪尖  說我什麼都不知道\Nputs Frank at the center of this, and says I knew nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.26,0:03:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之後我們會回報他的誠實\NAnd then we'll reward him for his honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您是說特赦嗎\NYou mean a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.59,0:03:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想讓你跟他去談\NI want you to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓我自己陷於危險之中嗎\NAnd put myself at risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.18,0:03:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在不在政府供職了\NWell, you're not part of this administration anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:03:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有法律規定你不能去拜訪雷蒙德·塔斯克\NThere's no law that says you can't pay Raymond Tusk a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作為回報  辭職也不非得永久有效  琳達\NAnd in return, resignations don't have to last forever, Linda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我這麼做  您得和我保持距離  越遠越好\NIf I do this, you have to be a million miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特莉莎和我會去戴維營\NTricia and I'll go to Camp David.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不算特別遠  但也夠了\NIt's not a million miles away, but it'll do the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.52,0:04:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以對琳達下手  調查她的過去\NI can go after Linda. Dig into her past --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.50,0:04:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞定她解決不了大問題\NNeutralizing her won't neutralize the bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是總統想要我的命\NIt's the president that's after blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.58,0:04:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他打算怎麼做\NThen what's his move?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.60,0:04:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不能要求我辭職  只能把我擠走\NHe can't ask me to resign. He'd have to force me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.48,0:04:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要擠走我的話  如果我是他\NAnd to do that, if I were him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定會回去找最初成就我的人\NI would return to the hand that first fed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-雷蒙德·塔斯克嗎  -沒錯\N- Raymond Tusk? - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會  他要是把你捲進去  他自己也難保\NNo, he'd have to implicate himself to implicate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非他能得到赦免\NNot if he gets a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.28,0:04:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是唯一只有總統才能開出的條件\NIt's the one thing that only a president can offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.39,0:04:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克是個手榴彈  如果他赦免了他...\NTusk is a hand grenade. If he pardons him --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯  塔斯克是個手榴彈\NYou're right. Tusk is a hand grenade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.03,0:04:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得拽下保險栓  朝沃克扔過去\Nand we need to pull the pin and throw him at Walker
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.20,0:04:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否則就是沃克拽下保險栓  扔向我們了\Nbefore Walker pulls the pin and throws him at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.30,0:05:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得和雷蒙德見面  一對一\NI want to meet with Raymond, one on one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.95,0:05:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我代表你去談吧\NLet me speak on your behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-這樣的話  如果有人發現  -我瞭解雷蒙德\N- That way if anyone finds -- -I know Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.09,0:05:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只會對我做出回應\NHe won't respond to anyone but me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的聽證會安排在什麼時候\NWhen's his hearing scheduled?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.46,0:05:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,後天下午兩點\NUh, day after tomorrow. Two p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那我們還有40個小時行動  -是  先生\N- That gives us 40 hours to make it happen. - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是我的手機\NI think it's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.74,0:07:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,賽斯  現在可是凌晨四點\NSeth, it's four in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.17,0:07:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼時候\NWhen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你跟她一起去\NI want you to go with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.64,0:07:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我這就去徵求洛克蘭的批准  -謝謝\N- I'll get it cleared with Rockland right now. -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.93,0:07:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,密查姆說飛機30分鐘內就能準備好\NMeechum says the plane will be ready in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.40,0:07:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行  好\NOkay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.14,0:07:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得只是恐慌癥發作\NYou think it was just a panic attack
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-還是她真打算...  -我不知道\N- or was she really trying -- -I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們要她留院觀察一整夜就夠糟了\NIt was bad enough they felt they had to keep her overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.58,0:07:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我給白宮醫生辦公室打個電話\NI'm gonna call the White House physician's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.21,0:07:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-看看他們能不能推薦什麼人 -好\N- see if they can recommend anyone. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.03,0:07:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-等等  我的手機  -在你手裏\N- Oh, wait. My phone. - It's in your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.23,0:07:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我今晚回來\NI'll be back sometime tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彈劾是我們唯一的機會\NImpeachment is our only chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這些席位在中期選舉中仍處於爭奪狀態\NHere are the seats that are still in contention in the midterms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.00,0:07:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這13個我們再怎麼努力也會失去\NThese 13 we're gonna lose no matter what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但即便我們拿下剩下所有席位\NBut even if we win all the rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們也只有五個席位的優勢\Nthat only leaves us with a five-seat majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.64,0:07:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要麼保黨  要麼保總統\NWe either save the party or we save the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.64,0:08:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何人反對彈劾的人\NAnyone who votes against impeachment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.29,0:08:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在選舉前都會受到攻擊性廣告的攻擊\Nis gonna get pommeled by attack ads between now and election day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已經有多少票了\NHow many do you have already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.06,0:08:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們需要18票  我只有六票\NWe need 18. I have six.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.72,0:08:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那還要爭取12票\NSo, 12 more to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.00,0:08:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唐納德  我知道這是個很大的人情\NLook, Donald, I know this is a big ask
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你更想把注意力放在政策上  不...\Nand you prefer to focus on policy and not --
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,傑姬  不用說了  我加入\NJackie, you can stop. I'm on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-真的嗎  - 百分百\N- Really? - 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不得不說  我有點驚訝\NI have to say I'm a little surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.67,0:08:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把那些手推車推進休息室的時候  你說\NWhen you rolled those dollies into the cloakroom you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.21,0:08:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"跟我合作  我不是弗蘭克·安德伍德"\N"Work with me. I'm not Frank Underwood."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.62,0:08:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然後你幫我通過了經濟刺激方案\NAnd then you helped get my stimulus package through,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你信守了諾言\Njust like you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.06,0:08:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這次你有什麼期望呢\NAnd what do you expect this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.39,0:08:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你永遠不會成為弗蘭克·安德伍德\NThat you never become Frank Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要知道  如果我們成功了  他會取代沃克\NYou must realize if we're successful, he will replace Walker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.62,0:08:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不喜歡弗蘭克  但我更討厭成為少數黨\NI don't like Frank. but I hate being in the minority even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.53,0:08:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能讓共和黨同時執掌國會兩院\NWe can't let the Republicans control both houses of Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.65,0:09:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我加入領導層以來  你變了\NYou've changed since I joined the leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是更懂得如何玩這場遊戲了\NJust getting better at playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看來頑固不化這詞不太對\NI guess you can teach an old liberal new tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.64,0:09:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看來是的\NI guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:09:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴我你還需要誰\NSo, tell me who you still need.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的律師說我贏得庭審的概率是一半一半\NMy lawyers are saying 50/50 that I survive a trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不太滿意這個數字\NNow, I'm not a big fan of those odds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我願意接受\Nbut I'm willing to take 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.32,0:09:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你的律師說這事就看運氣\NIf your lawyers are putting it at a coin toss,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你是花錢雇了一群太過樂觀的人\Nthen you're paying them too much to be overly optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.16,0:09:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎麼能信任加勒特\NAnd how can I trust Garrett?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.47,0:09:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他背叛了20年的友誼\NHe turned his back on 20 years of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.64,0:09:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也可以這麼說你\NHe could accuse you of the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.83,0:09:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這地球上沒有人\NWell, nobody on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比我更想看弗蘭克·安德伍德進監獄了\Nwants to see Frank Underwood go to jail more than I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是不想到時跟他關在一起\NI just don't want to be sharing a cell with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.45,0:09:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這種事不會發生的\NThat won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只給了我加勒特的口頭承諾\NAll you've given me to go on is Garrett's word.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.81,0:09:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想讓你說出實情\NHe's asking you to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做正確的事的人必有好報\NGood things happen to those who do the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們就指望弗蘭克會跪地求饒\NAnd you just expect Frank to lie down,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.34,0:10:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,舉旗認輸嗎\Nthrow in the towel, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,連求饒的機會也不給他\NWe don't even give him the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.72,0:10:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的證詞會讓他全無反擊之力\NYour testimony knocks him out cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請稍等\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼事  啊  多謝你\NYes? Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.95,0:10:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請等一下\NHold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.87,0:10:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給你\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我妻子送的小禮物\NCare package from my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.50,0:10:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那麼  請繼續\NNow, you were saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得提醒你一下  她現在完全不在狀態\NI just want to warn you, she's not herself right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.12,0:10:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們不得不給她服用了大劑量的藥物\NThey had to put her on some heavy doses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.55,0:10:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼藥\NOf what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.73,0:10:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主要是碳酸鋰[抗躁狂藥]\NLithium, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不然就得留院觀察30天了\NIt was either that or commit her for 30 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.92,0:11:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她剛吃了藥  可能有點...\NNow she just took some, so she might be a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.90,0:11:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅根\NMegan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.27,0:11:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別碰我\NStop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.39,0:11:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你媽媽告訴我他們從湖裏救起了你\NYour mom told me they found you in the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:11:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你管我呢\NWhat do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:11:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常關心你\NI care very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.98,0:12:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才怪\NNo, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒人會利用他們關心的人\NYou don't use somebody you care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,娼妓\NWhore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蕩婦\NSlut.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.46,0:12:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婊子\NBitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叛徒\NTraitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們就是這麼說我的\NThat's what they call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.19,0:12:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,發郵件  在網上\NIn my mail. Online.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.05,0:12:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真希望我沒打那通電話\NI wish I'd never called.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.95,0:12:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真希望我沒見過你\NI wish I'd never met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.80,0:12:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你說什麼我信什麼  真是蠢透了\NI feel so stupid believing what you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.35,0:12:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我還以為你真心關心我\NThinking that you did care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我本來都快恢復了\NI was getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.48,0:12:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這全怨你\NYou did this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我每吃一片藥  都會想到他\NEvery time I take one of these I think of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.34,0:12:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下來我想到的\NAnd the next face I think of?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.31,0:12:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是你\NIt's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.23,0:13:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得被利用了  我很遺憾\NI'm sorry that you felt used.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.50,0:13:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒有利用你\NYou weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.61,0:13:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是\NI just, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像我說的  政治風向變了  而且\Nlike I told you, the political landscape shifted and --
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.79,0:13:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我們發現\Nand we found...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅根\NMegan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我收到你的短信了\NI got your text.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道我不該聯繫你  但我覺得\NI know I shouldn't be reaching out to you, but I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.24,0:13:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  沒關係  我很高興你通知了我\NNo, that doesn't matter. I'm glad you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.09,0:13:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她怎麼樣\NHow is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.58,0:14:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狀態很不好\NIn bad shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.52,0:14:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說實話我很吃驚他們還敢讓她離開醫院\NI'm surprised they even let her out of the hospital, to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.09,0:14:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什麼我能做的嗎\NIs there anything I can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.25,0:14:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用不用我聯繫她的親人  親自去探望她\NShould I contact her family or go out there myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.46,0:14:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們最好不要打擾她了\NWe should probably leave her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.47,0:14:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你還好嗎\NAre you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.68,0:14:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒事  你呢\NI'm fine. How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還撐得住\NUh, holding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.42,0:14:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和律師商量了一整天\NSpent the whole day talking to lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.58,0:14:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這對孩子們太不容易了\NIt's hard on the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.31,0:14:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們既窘迫又害怕\NThey're embarrassed and frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.76,0:14:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們會熬過去的\NBut we'll get through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.26,0:14:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得你和加勒特的講話很感人\NI thought the speech you and Garrett gave was very moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,似乎起了點作用\NWell, it seems to have helped some.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.17,0:14:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其實我是受你的啟發\NI was inspired by you, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你敢於在電視上承認墮過胎\NWhen you admitted to the abortion on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.11,0:14:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真相往往很有衝擊力\NThe truth is a powerful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特莉莎  我想向你道歉\NTricia, I want to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.95,0:15:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼\NWhat for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.67,0:15:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的家庭所經歷的這些變故\NI feel partly responsible for everything
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.61,0:15:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得我有一部分責任\Nyour family's going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.37,0:15:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我建議你們去見咨詢師\NIt was my suggestion that you get counseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.48,0:15:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早知今日  我當初就什麼都不會說了\NAnd had I known then, I never would have said a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.34,0:15:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克萊爾  別這麼說  見咨詢師效果很好\NClaire, please. Counseling was a godsend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加勒特和我需要幫助\NGarrett and I needed help,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.20,0:15:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且也確實起了作用\Nand it's made things better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.58,0:15:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我應該感謝你\NI should be thanking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還要感謝你把梅根的事告訴我\NAnd thank you for letting me know about Megan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能去看她  真是好心\NIt was kind of you to make that trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是個好人  克萊爾\NYou're a good person, Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保重\NBe well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我估計你是想說聽證會的事\NI take it this is about my hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.34,0:17:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是不是沃克聯繫過你了\NDid Walker get to you first?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.59,0:17:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒比你快多少\NBarely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有時候  哪怕只快一點也足夠了\NBut sometimes barely is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.81,0:17:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他肯定提出給你特赦\NI'm sure he offered you a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.25,0:17:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提供競爭對手給不了的  才是高招\NAlways better to offer something your competitor can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.41,0:17:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我能給你更好的\NOh, but I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.14,0:17:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,據我所知  憲法規定的\NThe last time I read the Constitution,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.18,0:17:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統能給的最有價值的東西也就是...\Nthe most a vice president could offer was, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:17:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陪陪笑臉  遞遞眼色了\Nsmile and a wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.16,0:18:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我已經證明我不是一般的副總統\NI think I've proven that I'm not your typical vice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.13,0:18:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一般或不一般  你都輸了  弗蘭克\NTypical or not, you've lost, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.29,0:18:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我還有出路  你沒有\NI have an out. You don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加勒特撐不過彈劾的\NGarrett will not survive impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你絕不能否認\NIf there's one skill you can't deny,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.46,0:18:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我拉選票的能力\Nit's my ability to whip votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.80,0:18:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是在眾議院  不是在參議院\NIn the House. Not in the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.92,0:18:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但依據憲法  我是參議院的主席\NWhich the Constitution makes me the President of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.10,0:18:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也看到我是怎麼通過福利改革了\NAnd you saw what I did with entitlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.87,0:18:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,傲慢使你自以為了不起了  弗蘭克\NHubris is giving you delusions of grandeur, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.14,0:18:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算沃克僥倖逃過一劫\NLet's say Walker squeaks by.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  你能得到特赦\NYes, you get your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你卻把自己跟一個\NBut you've bound yourself at the hip
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.52,0:18:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有任何政治資本的人拴在一起了\Nto a man who has zero political capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.94,0:18:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他被定罪  我們都要坐牢\NAnd if he gets convicted, we all go to jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.27,0:18:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誰都沒有特赦了\NThere's no pardon for anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我願意賭一把\NI'll roll the dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德  用你的商業頭腦想想\NRaymond, think like a businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.71,0:19:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不就是靠盡量減小風險積累財富的嗎\NHaven't you built a fortune by minimizing risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.72,0:19:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這不就是你這些年用錢堆砌國會\NIsn't that why you stacked Congress all these years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引領加勒特當上總統\Nwhy you guided Garrett to the Oval,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.29,0:19:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留我當黨鞭的原因嗎\Nand why you kept me on as Whip?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.55,0:19:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沃克是個垃圾股  貶值得快\NWalker is a junk bond quickly depreciating,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我可以迅速解決和中國的貿易戰\Nwhereas I can end the conflict with China
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還能保你不坐牢\Nand keep you in the black.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.97,0:19:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你沒法保證改善和中國的關係\NYou can't promise better relations with China.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.58,0:19:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我破壞的  我也能修復\NI wrecked them. I can repair them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.53,0:19:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一起合作吧  就如我們起初打算的那樣\NNow let's work together, as we always intended to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等你被關進棺材大的牢房裏\NWhen they put you in that box barely bigger than a coffin,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:19:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,記住今晚這美妙的音樂吧\Nremember how beautiful the music was tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.10,0:19:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或許能讓你稍微好受點\NIt might give you some small degree of comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普契尼太傷感  我喜歡積極向上的\NPuccini's a downer. I prefer something much more optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.51,0:20:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們不肯放布朗  審判日期已經定了\NThey won't touch Brown. The trial date is set.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們可以減少指控\NThey can reduce the charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,達拉斯不願讓步  如果我繼續施壓\NDallas won't give. If I keep pressing,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.75,0:20:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會顯得可疑\Nit'll start to look suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.90,0:20:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能確保你不被起訴\NWhat I can do is make sure you don't get prosecuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有我不再替你工作\NAnd I stop working for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.54,0:20:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不全是  我跟檢察官說\NNot quite. I told the U.S. Attorney
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.60,0:20:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們想讓你為我們工作\Nthat we wanted to bring you on with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,網絡恐怖主義分局  你的案底將一筆勾銷\NCyber terrorism division. You'd get a clean slate, as --
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.06,0:20:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門都沒有\NNo fucking way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.66,0:20:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們不會就那麼放棄你\NThey're not gonna let your case go
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.23,0:20:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非我們給他們充分的理由\Nunless we give them a compelling reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.18,0:20:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-沒別的  -我跟調查局鬥爭了半輩子\N- There's no o - I've spent half my life fighting the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.59,0:20:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只能這麼說\NIt's the only way I could sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓住機會  嘉文\NTake this opportunity, Gavin,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.16,0:20:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,趁他們還沒改主意\Nbefore they change their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.23,0:20:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要見道格拉斯·斯坦普\NI want to meet with Douglas Stamper.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行  我們說好了我幫你找出路\NNo. The deal was I find you a way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.62,0:21:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說好的是你幫布朗脫身並且還我自由\NNo, the deal was you help out Brown and you give me my freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.18,0:21:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你沒為布朗辦成任何事\NYou haven't done shit for Brown,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.35,0:21:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還想繼續控制我\Nand you still want to keep me under your thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.89,0:21:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓我見斯坦普  否則一切免談\NSo I meet Stamper, or any kinda deal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德沒答應\NRaymond said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他沒表態\NHe said neither yes nor no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.23,0:21:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會繼續施壓\NI'll keep the pressure on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他還是有可能指證你\NSo he could still name you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  一切皆有可能\NHe could. Anything's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.55,0:21:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得阻止他\NWell, you have to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.71,0:21:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在嘗試\NI'm trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.96,0:21:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘗試遠遠不夠  弗蘭西斯\NWell, trying's not enough, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.58,0:21:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我總不能在聽證會上坐在他旁邊\NWell, I can't sit next to him in the hearing room
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.38,0:21:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿槍抵著他頭\Nwith a gun to his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.70,0:21:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這聽起來像在找借口\NNow that sounds like an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.22,0:21:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事實就是這樣\NIt's a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.51,0:21:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你答應過  我不用做最壞的打算\NYou promised me I wasn't going to have to prepare for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.54,0:21:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也打算信守諾言\NAnd I intend to keep that promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想確保  我們都要確定會沒事\NWell, I want to be sure. I want both of us to be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.92,0:21:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一萬無一失的辦法  就是讓沃克阻止他\NThe only surefire way is for Walker to call him off personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就去辦\NThen make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.87,0:21:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能逼一個拿我當敵人的人\NI cannot force a man who thinks I'm his enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.22,0:21:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,突然把我當朋友\Nto suddenly call me his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.65,0:22:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我該做的都做了\NI've done what I had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.12,0:22:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在輪到你了\NNow you do what you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.29,0:22:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勾引他  把你的心交給他\NSeduce him. Give him your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.81,0:22:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挖出來放在他手上\NCut it out and put it in his fucking hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.24,0:23:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,親愛的總統先生\NDear Mr. President,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.81,0:23:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在用我離開桑蒂諾時\NI'm writing on an Underwood portable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我父親給我的安德伍德打字機給您寫信\Nmy father gave me when I left for the Sentinel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.99,0:23:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我父親將它給我時說了些話\NIt was the words my father said when he gave it to me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.83,0:23:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比這台七十多年的機器更讓我能產生共鳴\Nthat have resonated even more than this 70-year-old machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.99,0:23:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"這個安德伍德建立了一個商業帝國"他說\N"This Underwood built an empire," He said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.28,0:23:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"現在該你去建立一個屬於你自己的帝國了"\N"Now you go and build one of your own."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.93,0:23:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這些話一直激勵著我\NThose words have been a large part of what has motivated my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.25,0:23:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只用這台打字機寫過另一封信\NI've only written one other letter with these keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.99,0:24:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那封信不辱使命  希望這次也一樣\NIt did not fail me then. I hope it will not fail me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.95,0:24:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您說我想削弱您\NYou said I wanted to diminish you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.15,0:24:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,實際上  我沒有\NThe truth is, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.11,0:24:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您說我想在2016年跟您競爭\NYou said I wanted to challenge you in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.00,0:24:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,實際上  我沒有\NThe truth is, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.95,0:24:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您說我想自己當總統\NYou said I wanted the presidency for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.56,0:24:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,實際上\NThe truth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.69,0:24:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的確想\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.33,0:24:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪個政客沒想過\NWhat politician hasn't dreamed about what it would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.63,0:24:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宣誓執掌國家最高權力\Nto take the oath of the highest office of our land?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.66,0:24:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾盯著您的總統辦公桌看  覬覦它\NI've stared at your desk in the Oval and coveted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.04,0:24:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,權力  威望\NThe power, the prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.26,0:24:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些東西對我這樣一個來自南卡羅來納州\NThose things have a strong pull on someone like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.81,0:24:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一座小鎮  曾一無所有的人來說有致命的吸引力\Nwho came from a small South Carolina town with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.60,0:24:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但自您就職時起\NBut since you assumed office,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.18,0:24:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我唯一的目標就是為您而戰\Nmy only aim has been to fight for you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.76,0:24:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,與您並肩作戰\Nand alongside you,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.93,0:24:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,無論是在國會還是現在\Nwhether that be in Congress or as now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在這場彈劾之戰中\Nthe battle over impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或許有一天  我有幸能成為總統\NMaybe one day I'll have my chance to serve as president,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.07,0:24:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但絕不是您在任期間\Nbut not while you are the nation's leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.67,0:25:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在您身上  我看到了勇敢\NAnd in you, sir, I see a brave man.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.80,0:25:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到了正直  您是我願意永遠追隨的總統\NA just man. A president whom I would follow anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.04,0:25:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,無論我們遇到多大的阻力\Nno matter how strong the wind blows against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.11,0:25:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一件事我從沒對任何人說過\NI want to tell you something I have never told anyone:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.51,0:25:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我13歲那年在穀倉裏撞見我父親\NWhen I was 13 I walked in on my father in the barn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.54,0:25:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把獵槍伸到嘴裏\NThere was a shotgun in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.24,0:25:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他朝我擺了擺手說道"過來  弗蘭西斯\NHe waved me over. "Come here, Francis," He said.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.95,0:25:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,替我扣動扳機"\N"Pull the trigger for me."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.25,0:25:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為他沒有勇氣自己做\NBecause he didn't have the courage to do it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.20,0:25:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說"不  爸爸"  就離開了\NI said, "No, Papa," And walked out,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.62,0:25:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他永遠沒有那個勇氣\Nknowing he would never find that courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.58,0:25:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下來的七年裏  我父親生不如死\NThe next seven years were hell for my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.07,0:25:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我母親和我更加痛苦\Nbut even more hell for my mother and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.00,0:25:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他令我們都苦不堪言\NHe made all of us miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.09,0:25:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,酗酒  絕望  暴力\NDrinking, despair, violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.29,0:25:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一生中唯一的後悔  就是當時沒扣動扳機\NMy only regret in life is that I didn't pull that trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.42,0:25:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死亡對他來說會是種解脫\NHe would have been better off in the grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.96,0:25:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有他我們也會過得更好\Nand we would have been better off without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.94,0:26:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不會讓您陷入同樣的境地\NI'm not going to put you in the same position
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.90,0:26:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像我父親對我那樣\Nas my father put me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,信中附上了一張紙\NYou will find enclosed on a separate sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.89,0:26:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上面供認了所有您被指控的罪名\Na confession to the crimes you have been accused of.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.46,0:26:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是假的  但我的簽名會使它們成真\NThey're false words, but my signature will make them true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.78,0:26:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有必要的話就用吧\NUse them if you must.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.41,0:26:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果您真的認為我的所作所為都是為了自己\NIf you truly believe that I have only served myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.06,0:26:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那麼我已經永遠失去了您的信任\Nthen I have forever lost your trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.84,0:26:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我現在能做的  只有獻出自己的自由以保住您\NAll I can do now is give you my freedom to save your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.59,0:26:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說過我會替您承擔責任\NI said I would take the fall for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.93,0:26:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在我把方法告訴了您\Nand now I give you the means to make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.78,0:26:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要自己扣動扳機\NI am pulling the trigger myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.07,0:26:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為了實現夢想我們都要做出犧牲\NWe all must make sacrifices to achieve our dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.46,0:26:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有時為了大局必須犧牲自己\Nbut sometimes we must sacrifice ourselves for the greater good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.38,0:26:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做出這樣的犧牲是我的榮幸\NIt is my honor to make such a sacrifice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.06,0:26:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您忠實的朋友  至少我仍這樣認為\NYour loyal friend, still in my heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.96,0:26:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即便您不這麼想  弗蘭西斯\Nif not in yours, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.06,0:27:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,憲法列出了一般原則\NThe Constitution sets forth the general principles --
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.65,0:27:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  總統的電話\NSir? The president's on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.85,0:27:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.76,0:27:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我收到信了  我讓特莉莎也看了\NI got your letter. I had Tricia read it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.89,0:27:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很糾結  弗蘭克  一半認為你是懇誠的\NI'm torn, Frank. Half of me wants to think you're genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.57,0:27:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一半卻一個字也不信\NThe other half doesn't trust a word of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.53,0:27:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特莉莎也這麼想嗎\NDoes Tricia feel the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.27,0:27:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她信任克萊爾  所以她也想相信你\NShe believes in Claire, which inclines her to believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.41,0:27:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我字字發自肺腑\NI meant every syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.86,0:27:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想讓您百分之百地相信\NI wanted you to know beyond a shadow of a doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.55,0:27:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我願做任何必要的事\Nthat I am willing to do whatever is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.31,0:27:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那麼  我為什麼拋不開疑慮呢\NWell, then why can't I shake the shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.23,0:28:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為我是個騙子  先生\NBecause I'm a liar, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.36,0:28:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為我無所顧忌  甚至可以說沒有同情心\NBecause I lack scruples and some would even say compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.38,0:28:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但那只是我展示給世人的一面\NBut that's just the image that I present to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.92,0:28:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為那能使人害怕  讓人尊敬我\Nbecause it elicits fear and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.84,0:28:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我不是那樣的人\NBut it is not who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.54,0:28:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望我的信能向您證明這一點\NMy hope was that my letter would prove that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.31,0:28:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  就算你說的都是真的\NWell, even if you are being genuine,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.00,0:28:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對我也沒什麼用\Nthat doesn't do much for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想躲過彈劾\NI won't survive impeachment
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.31,0:28:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能只靠我和我的副總統關繫好\Nbecause I got along with my vice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.89,0:28:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  我同意  您需要的不只是我的好意\NNo, I agree you need more than my good intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.37,0:28:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,證明給我看  弗蘭克\NProof. That's what I want to see, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.26,0:28:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別光承擔責任  我要結果\NAnd not just falling on the sword. Show me results.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.33,0:28:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那樣我會重新考慮你是否值得信任\NAnd then I'll reconsider whether you're worth any of my trust at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.51,0:28:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您是說投票\NYou're talking votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.68,0:28:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  拉票是你的強項\NYeah. Whipping votes was your strong suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.02,0:28:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想看到你那一面\NThat's the side of you I want to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.23,0:28:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經開始著手了  先生\NI've already begun, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.10,0:28:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是嗎  得到票數了嗎\NYeah? You have a count?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.47,0:28:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有個大概  形勢一直在變化\NAn approximation. The sands keep shifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.06,0:29:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們能得到眾議院的支持嗎\NWell, can we survive the House or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.93,0:29:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有可能  但是傑姬·夏普在阻撓\NPossibly, but Jackie Sharp is making it very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.62,0:29:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴我票數\NGive me numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.92,0:29:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她需要18票  已經拉到過半\NOver half of the 18 that she needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.69,0:29:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我想從參議院下手\Nwhich is why I'd like to start focusing on the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.70,0:29:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不覺得現在行動有點早嗎\NDon't you think that's premature?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.32,0:29:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們必須有所準備\NWe should be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.03,0:29:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重中之重就是確保您不被定罪\NThe key battle is making sure that you avoid conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.47,0:29:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你繼續拉票  有消息告訴我\NWell, you keep whipping, you keep getting me information,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就等你電話了\NI'll answer your calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.17,0:29:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但別以為你我就此相安無事了  弗蘭克\NBut don't take that as a sign of reconciliation, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.99,0:29:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會感激收穫  先生\NI'll sing for my supper, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.33,0:29:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我不會以為我能不勞而獲\NI don't expect it for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.89,0:29:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們明早再商量\NLet's talk again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.10,0:29:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝您  總統先生\NThank you, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.69,0:29:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你說你想有選擇餘地\NYou said you wanted options.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.20,0:29:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但弗蘭克讓我沒得選  他坑了我\NFrank didn't leave me options. He fucked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.00,0:29:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你和塔斯克沆瀣一氣  先把他坑了\NYou fucked him first when you sided with Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.27,0:29:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但誰管中間過程怎樣\NBut who cares what happened each inning?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.29,0:29:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有最終比分才算數\NIt's the final score that counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.51,0:29:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在他麾下八年  為他跑前跑後\NEight years I spent busting my ass in this office.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.60,0:29:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看來還是躲不過為他賣命\NI can't seem to escape it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.07,0:29:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是幫我們還是不幫\NYou gonna help us or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.47,0:29:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要知道我有什麼好處\NI need to know what I gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.48,0:29:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你會得到關照的  -說具體點\N- You'll be taking care of. - Specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.99,0:30:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等到塵埃落定  再看看要怎麼辦吧\NWe'll see what makes sense when all the chips have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.31,0:30:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你是要我悶頭往懸崖下跳\NSo you just want me to leap off a cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.83,0:30:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,指望著運氣好摔不死嗎\Nand hope for a soft landing beneath?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.50,0:30:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在誰都不會要你  除了我們\NNo one will touch you now. Nobody except us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.10,0:30:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們就是你最好的運氣\NWe're as soft as you're gonna get.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.14,0:30:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能在白宮給我一官半職嗎\NA job at the White House?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.53,0:30:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這我說不准\NNo promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.53,0:30:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,結果如何取決於你的\NOther than something commensurate
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.14,0:30:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,忠誠度和經驗\Nwith your loyalty and experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.64,0:30:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我完全可以就此抽身  開始新的生活\NI could just walk away from it all. Start a new life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.30,0:30:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你抽不了身  你知道你做不到\NNo, you can't. You know you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.19,0:30:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,離了國會山  你只會衰萎\NYou'd wither away anywhere but the Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.89,0:30:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管你怎麼騙自己\NIt's never been about the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.32,0:30:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你做這一行不是為了錢\Nno matter what you tell yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.99,0:30:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跳槽的時候  弗蘭克求我留下\NWhen I left, Frank begged me to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.75,0:30:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說"這是權和錢二選一"\N"Power versus money," He said.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.80,0:30:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別屈尊加入那些繳富人稅的人\NDon't reduce myself to a tax bracket.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.17,0:30:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說得對  但我不認為他會求你\NHe was right. And I doubt he begged.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.13,0:30:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他對了一半\NHe was half right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.16,0:30:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有權力握在手裏  就比錢有用\NPower is better than money for as long as it lasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.43,0:30:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但權力總會滑出手心\NBut it never lasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.64,0:30:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的回答是什麼\NWhat's your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.35,0:31:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你當了黨鞭之後變得更冷血了\NYou've gotten colder since you've taken over this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.74,0:31:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣辦事容易些\NIt makes things easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.96,0:31:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是對外嗎\NOn the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.14,0:31:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,內外皆是\NAnd the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.27,0:31:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你  傑姬\NI miss you, Jackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.77,0:31:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打算合作的話  就告訴我\NTell me if you'll cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.40,0:31:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你哥哥在議員手下幹得如何\NHow's your brother enjoying working with the congressman?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.62,0:31:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我接個電話\NOh, excuse me one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.58,0:31:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.13,0:31:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要你打給塔斯克  告訴他交易取消\NI want you to call Tusk. Tell him the deal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.60,0:31:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-什麼  -你說得對\N- What? - You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.54,0:31:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想冒此風險\NI don't want to take the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.05,0:31:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我已經和他談過了\NBut I already spoke to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就再和他談談  告訴他特赦沒戲了\NWell, so speak to him again. And tell him there's no pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.54,0:31:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  我起初對這策略確實有些懷疑\NSir, I -- I -- I was skeptical of this strategy at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.29,0:31:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們已經選了這條路  就該走到底\Nbut now that we've gone down this road, we should stick to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.30,0:31:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琳達  你還想回來做幕僚長嗎\NLinda, do you still want your job back?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.84,0:31:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當然  先生\NOf course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.35,0:31:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就打給他\NThen make the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.97,0:32:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想先看看眾議院的結果\NI'd rather see what happens in the House
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.26,0:32:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再決定要不要幫你們\Nbefore I get involved in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.66,0:32:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果你能表現出對總統堅定的支持\NBut if you came out vigorously in defense of the President,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.30,0:32:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能會讓司法委員會覺得...\Nit might convince the Judiciary Committee --
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.96,0:32:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說實話  我並不是很想\NTo be honest, I'm not particularly inclined
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.67,0:32:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幫沃克的忙\Nto be doing Walker any favors.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.12,0:32:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邁克爾  我知道他撤銷了你的國務卿提名\NNow, Michael, I know he revoked your nomination.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.66,0:32:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他完全沒有為我爭取\NHe didn't fight for me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.00,0:32:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那時剛剛當選  還沒有足夠的...\NWell, he'd just been elected. He wasn't in a position to --
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.47,0:32:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才怪  他明明有這權力\NWrong. He had a clear mandate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.03,0:32:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他完全可以支持我\NHe was in a strong position to defend me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.65,0:32:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你說得對\NYou're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.32,0:32:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我是總統  我不會那麼輕易放棄\NIf I had been President I wouldn't have given in so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.06,0:32:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會在那篇文章曝光後堅定支持你\NI would've stuck by you after that article came to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.51,0:32:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老實說  如果國務卿是你而不是杜蘭特\NIn fact, if you'd been our secretary of state instead of Durant,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.50,0:32:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們和中國的關係或許就不會這麼差了\NI don't think we'd be in the mess we are with China.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.60,0:32:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但事實是  如果換了我\NBut the truth is, I wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.50,0:32:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不會提名你做國務卿\Nnominated you for secretary of state in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.92,0:32:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會提名你做財政部長\NI would have nominated you for secretary of treasury.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.18,0:32:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為你在經濟領域的專業知識\NBecause your expertise in economics is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.15,0:32:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比你的外交知識強得多\Neven better than your grasp on foreign affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.11,0:32:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我是總統  你就會做財政部長\NNo, if I were president, you'd be secretary of treasury.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.63,0:32:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你是總統...\NIf you were president.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.44,0:32:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.84,0:33:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能這樣\NYou can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼回事\NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.17,0:33:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是弗蘭克搗的鬼嗎\NWas it Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.25,0:33:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琳達  聽我說\NLinda, listen to me --
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.85,0:33:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明白\NI understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.47,0:33:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.30,0:33:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,交易取消了\NThe deal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.18,0:33:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她說原因了嗎\NDid she say why?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.98,0:33:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有  只說他改主意了\NNo. Other than he changed his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.78,0:33:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但肯定是因為弗蘭克\NBut it must be Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.74,0:33:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們還是按原計劃來\NThen we go back to the original plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.46,0:33:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯  和以前一樣拒不解釋\NThat's right. You plead the Fifth just like you did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.86,0:33:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這就是出政治鬧劇\NThis is political theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.86,0:33:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我們可以矇混過關然後關注  -天吶\N- We get past it and focus on the - Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.43,0:33:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼了\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷米·丹頓自願去鄧巴那裏作證  就是現在\NRemy Danton is volunteering to testify to Dunbar, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.99,0:33:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他自願的  不是被傳喚的嗎\NHe volunteered? He wasn't subpoenaed?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.22,0:33:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看起來是的\NLooks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.96,0:33:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要出賣我\NHe's gonna sell me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.68,0:33:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那樣的話他也會遭到起訴\NThat would open him up to prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.76,0:33:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非他受到了保護\NUnless he's being protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.42,0:34:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丹頓在哪\NWhere's Danton?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.01,0:34:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我給他助理打電話\NI'll call his assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.65,0:34:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否促成外資\NDid you or did you not facilitate foreign money
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.57,0:34:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,流入政治行動委員會\Nbeing funneled into political action committees?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.67,0:34:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根據我律師的意見\NOn the advice of my counsel,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.16,0:34:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我保留行使第五修正案的權利\NI reserve my right to invoke the Fifth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.89,0:34:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮山德聲稱你不僅是促成了此事\NXander Feng claims you not only facilitated,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更是最初的策劃者\Nyou orchestrated the scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.30,0:34:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你如何回應這項證詞\NNow what is your response to that testimony?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.79,0:34:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根據我律師的意見  我保留我的權利\NOn the advice of my counsel, I reserve my right to --
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.50,0:34:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天可以一直保留你的權利  塔斯克先生\NYou can reserve your right all day long, Mr. Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.94,0:34:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但等你面對陪審團時\NBut when you appear in front of a grand jury,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.62,0:34:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我確信司法部門一定會起訴你\Nas I'm sure the Justice Department intends,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.50,0:34:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的沉默將使你垮台\Nyour silence will be your downfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.54,0:34:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,議員有問題要問嗎\NDoes the congressman have a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.59,0:34:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以躲著我們  先生\NYou can hide from us all you want, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.76,0:34:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卻躲不過與你平起平坐的陪審團\NYou cannot hide from a jury of your peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.14,0:34:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-主席先生  -就這樣吧  我說完了\N- Mr. Chairman. - That's it. I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.81,0:34:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我放棄我剩餘的時間\NI relinquish the remainder of my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.32,0:34:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下面交給田納西州女議員\NThe chair recognizes the congresswoman from Tennessee.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.91,0:34:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,12分鐘  女士\NYou have 12 minutes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.49,0:35:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克先生  我們捲入了與中國的貿易戰中\NMr. Tusk, our nation is currently embroiled in a trade war with China.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.58,0:35:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這嚴重挫傷了我國經濟\NIt has gutted our economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.73,0:35:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使我們的海軍處於險境\NIt has placed our navy in harm's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.48,0:35:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-而使我們陷入這困境的總統  -他知道\N- The president who put us there has -- He knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.06,0:35:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你說什麼\NExcuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.53,0:35:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的委託人保留\NMy client reserves the --
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.74,0:35:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他知道  你們不就是想知道這個嗎\NHe knew. Isn't that what you're all wondering?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.53,0:35:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請安靜\NQuiet, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.40,0:35:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道什麼  確切一些\NKnew what, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.65,0:35:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一套機制  它在過去10年裏\NThere was a mechanism by which a great many contributions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.70,0:35:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,貢獻了大量的捐助款\Nwere made over the last 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.20,0:35:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我仍然認為\NThe legality of this mechanism is something
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.59,0:35:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這套機制並不觸犯法律\Nthat I continue to believe is within the boundaries of the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.74,0:35:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但至於該機制本身  馮山德先生說得對\NBut as for the mechanism itself, Mr. Feng is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.26,0:35:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我策劃的  是我促成的\NI orchestrated it. I facilitated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.14,0:35:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統是知道的\NAnd the president knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.37,0:35:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丹頓剛剛取消了\NDanton just canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.81,0:35:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去他的吧  我們有塔斯克\NScrew Danton. We've got Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.06,0:36:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接通司法部長\NGet me the attorney general.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.85,0:36:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有這個必要  塔斯克先生\NThat won't be necessary, Mr. Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.91,0:36:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請和我們走一趟\NIf you'll come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.46,0:36:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真可惜\NThat's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.00,0:36:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,手銬也是我遺願清單中的一項呢\NHandcuffs were another item on my bucket list.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.81,0:36:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這邊走  先生  你有權保持沉默\NRight this way, sir. You have the right to remain silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.43,0:36:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你所說的一切將用來作為控告你的證據\NAnything you say can and will be used against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.66,0:36:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們談談條件吧  他在聽證會上很配合\NWe'll want a bond. For his cooperation in the hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.29,0:36:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,認罪了再談條件\NI'll talk bonds if you'll talk a plea.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.26,0:36:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人們對證詞的反應又快又強烈\NResponse to the testimony has been swift and vocal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.35,0:36:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抗議者從昨天起\NProtesters have been gathering in front of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.04,0:36:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,便聚集在白宮前\Nthe White House since yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.86,0:36:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要求沃克總統下台\Ndemanding President Walker's resignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.39,0:36:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一份網上請願書在過去24小時裏\NAnd an online petition has already accumulated
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.88,0:36:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已經獲得二十多萬人簽名\Nover 200,000 signatures in the past 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.85,0:36:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩院公開譴責總統的人數\NThe list of lawmakers publicly condemning the president
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.36,0:36:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越來越多\Nhas grown on both sides of the aisle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.58,0:36:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天下午  中國大使\NAnd this afternoon the Chinese ambassador
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.29,0:36:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也譴責了沃克政府\Nalso condemned the Walker administration,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.74,0:36:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,指責其瞞著北京與腐敗商人做交易\Nsaying China would not negotiate with a president
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.15,0:36:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說中國不會與這樣的總統進行談判\Nwho dealt with corrupt businessmen behind Beijing's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.77,0:37:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今  兩國的軍艦\NThis at a time when warships from both countries --
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.98,0:37:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,與此同時  總統與第一夫人\NMeanwhile the president and first lady
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.74,0:37:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍在戴維營閉門不出  尚未對華盛頓\Nremain bunkered at Camp David and have offered no public response
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.25,0:37:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最新的進展發表公開回應\Nto the most recent developments in Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.39,0:37:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們請到了《華爾街電訊報》的艾拉·薩伊德\NI'm here with Ayla Sayyad of the Wall Street Telegraph.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.89,0:37:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾拉  我必須先說\NAnd Ayla, I have to begin by saying that sources
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.66,0:37:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,據國會知情人士透露\Non the Hill are telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.32,0:37:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法委員會可能完全跳過辯論\Nthat the Judiciary Committee may bypass debate all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.73,0:37:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  委員會還沒有人正式發表這樣的聲明\NUh, no one on the committee has gone on record about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.18,0:37:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果不是委員會十分傾向於\NBut do you think these rumors would be circulating
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.88,0:37:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,建議眾議院啟動彈劾程序\Nif there weren't some sort of strong preference
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.06,0:37:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也不會有這種傳言了吧\Nto recommend the Articles of Impeachment to the House?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.24,0:37:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我認為幾乎可以肯定彈劾很受支持\NI think it's safe to assume there is strong support.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.88,0:37:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到的每份民調都顯示\NEvery poll I've seen shows
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.58,0:37:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很大一部分美國人希望更進一步\Nan overwhelming majority of Americans want this to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.99,0:37:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得政客們不會無視這一點\NI don't think politicians are going to ignore that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.19,0:37:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經和我的一些同事聊過了\NI've talked to a number of my colleagues already.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.58,0:37:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,民主黨這邊有些支持者\NThere's support on my side of the aisle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.48,0:37:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你有多少  -現在包括我在內有五個\N- Well, how many do you have? - Five at this point, including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.61,0:37:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就一共有60個了  還需要七個\NThat would put us at 60. We'd still need seven more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.54,0:37:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也看了昨晚的民調了\NYou've seen the overnight polls.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.23,0:37:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的支持率都降到個位數了\NHe's dipped down into the single digits.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.75,0:37:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想和我們一起發表公開聲明嗎\NAre you willing to make a public statement with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.16,0:37:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得事到如今\NI think the country could use
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.46,0:37:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩黨合作一下也不是壞事吧\Na little bipartisanship right now, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.39,0:37:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得他們在虛張聲勢嗎\NDo you think they're bluffing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.43,0:38:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為了動搖參議院那些仍在猶豫的人而耍的花招\NThat it's some sort of stunt to sway the undecideds in the Senate?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.30,0:38:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邁克爾·科恩小氣又記仇  先生\NMichael Kern is bitter and small-minded, sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.79,0:38:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果他們沒獲得足夠的支持\Nbut he wouldn't appear publicly with Mendoza
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.70,0:38:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不會和門多薩一同公開表態\Nif they didn't have the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.24,0:38:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以想像眾議院的情況比之前更糟了\NWell, I imagine we're worse off in the House than we were before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.96,0:38:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其實我本來和傑姬·夏普聊得還挺有成效\NIn fact, I had a very productive conversation with Jackie Sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.08,0:38:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她同意停止攻擊\NShe agreed to stop the attack
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.74,0:38:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要我們在中期選舉後支持她做多數黨領袖\Nif we give her our support for majority leader after the midterms.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.38,0:38:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但雷蒙德一提供他的證詞\NBut once Raymond gave his testimony,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.57,0:38:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她就打電話說交易取消\Nshe called to say the deal was off.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.42,0:38:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德真的給了我們很大打擊\NRaymond really has set us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.30,0:38:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我真想不通他為什麼要撒謊\NI can't fathom why he lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.92,0:38:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要報復我\NWell, it's retribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.49,0:38:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-為了什麼  能源危機嗎  -不是\N- For what? The energy crisis? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.99,0:38:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您給了他什麼好處嗎\NDid you offer him something?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.95,0:38:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德的證詞確實於我們不利\NWell, Raymond's testimony hurts,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.36,0:38:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但並沒有終結我們\Nbut it can't finish us off.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.78,0:38:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謊言是無法證明的\NIt's impossible to prove a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.85,0:38:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彈劾不可避免\NImpeachment is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.49,0:38:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在民眾輿論成了敵人  事實已經不重要了\NPublic opinion is the adversary now. Facts no longer matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.68,0:38:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您應該給科恩打個電話  跟他本人聊聊\NYou should give Kern a call. The personal touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.26,0:38:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他重新支持我們\NIf he came back to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.73,0:39:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別的民主黨可能就會膽怯退縮\Nit might make the other Democrats get cold feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.05,0:39:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國也在幫倒忙\NWell, China isn't helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.15,0:39:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,錢主席不回我的電話\NPresident Qian won't return my calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.08,0:39:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北京那邊肯定覺得我氣數已盡\NBeijing must smell death.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.76,0:39:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們只是在利用這個局面尋求籌碼\NThey're just exploiting the situation for leverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.75,0:39:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在先別考慮中國\NLet's not worry about China for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.66,0:39:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一步一步慢慢來  先生\NOne battle at a time, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.25,0:39:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我大概是完了  弗蘭克\NMaybe I'm finished, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.32,0:39:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也許我該接受  我們沒法全身而退了\NMaybe I need to start accepting that we won't pull out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.60,0:39:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生  我知道您累了\NMr. President, I know you're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.89,0:39:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道這一切讓您備受折磨\NI know this has been hell for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.63,0:39:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,確實  彈劾會是個嚴重的打擊\NAnd, yes, impeachment would be an awful blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.46,0:39:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們要在參議院浴血奮戰了\NWe'd have to fight tooth and nail in the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.46,0:39:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,確實  我們將不得不哀求和妥協\NAnd, yes, we'll have to beg and compromise
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.87,0:39:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重新賺回我們的政治資本\Nto regain our political capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.07,0:39:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們一定會勝利  先生\NBut we have it in us, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.32,0:39:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管拼得多麼頭破血流\NNo matter how many scars it leaves us with.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.43,0:39:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不僅僅是我們  弗蘭克\NIt's not just us, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.89,0:39:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有特莉莎  還有我的孩子們\NIt's Tricia. It's my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.39,0:39:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我整夜失眠  想著他們看到父親退縮\NI stay awake at night, thinking how much it would crush them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.11,0:39:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將是多大的打擊\Nseeing their father hauled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.32,0:39:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  不會那樣的  我不會允許\NSir, that won't happen because I won't let it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.76,0:39:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們遇上最糟的情況\NIf we're confronted by the worst,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.18,0:39:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我至少會確保您不會遭受牢獄之災\NI'll make sure you never step foot behind bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.93,0:40:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向您保證\NYou have my word on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.54,0:40:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他現在身處黑暗\NHe's in the darkness now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.59,0:40:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是唯一指路的明燈\NAnd I'm the only beacon of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.82,0:40:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在只要溫柔地把他引向礁石就可以了\NNow we gently guide him toward the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.72,0:40:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生  您還有我的信\NMr. President, you also still have my letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.98,0:40:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果您想走那條路  現在還不算太晚\NIt's not too late, if you want to use that option.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.75,0:40:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你留在國會比待在監獄更有用\NNo, you're more useful to me on the Hill than in handcuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.20,0:40:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會給科恩打電話\NI'll call Kern.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.85,0:40:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-晚安  先生  -晚安\N- Goodnight, sir. - Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.34,0:40:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格林告訴你多少\NHow much did Green tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.02,0:41:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,足夠讓我現身\NEnough that I showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.01,0:41:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他大概沒提到瑞秋·波斯納  是吧\NHe probably didn't mention Rachel Posner, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.33,0:41:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別擔心  他不知道\NDon't worry. He doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.04,0:41:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我知道\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.70,0:41:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把她藏在喬帕的一間公寓裏\NYou have her in an apartment in Joppa.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.83,0:41:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你的一舉一動\NI have your movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.46,0:41:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有你毀掉手機之前的短信\NI have your text messages before you destroyed your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.66,0:41:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不過這已經足夠了\NBut that's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.07,0:41:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信很多人都很想知道她知道的事\NI'll bet a lot of people would like to know what she knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.57,0:41:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你給我聽好了\NNow you listen to me very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.81,0:41:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管你以為你拿到了什麼\NWhatever you think you've got,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.03,0:41:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也不管你打算拿這些東西做什麼\Nwhatever you intend to do with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.75,0:41:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不會像格林那樣被敲詐牽著走\NI don't respond to extortion the same way that Green does.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.80,0:41:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格林給你的許諾\NWhat Green promised you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.30,0:41:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我瞬間就可以抵消\Nthat can be undone in a heartbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.28,0:41:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以才把你找來  確保不會變卦\NAnd that's why you're here. Make sure it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.05,0:41:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想要我的保護\NYou want my protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不信任格林或聯調局的任何人\NI don't trust Green or anyone at the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.90,0:42:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有誰知道\NWho else knows about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.90,0:42:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒人知道\NNo one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.48,0:42:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我為什麼要相信你\NWhy should I trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.08,0:42:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為我們兩個都輸不起  夥計\N'Cause we both have too much to lose, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.74,0:42:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿上衣服\NGet dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.69,0:42:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在幹什麼\NWhat -- what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.71,0:42:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿上衣服\NPut some clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.80,0:42:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼\NWhy -- why?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.31,0:42:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快點  我們走\NNow. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.41,0:42:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人聯繫你嗎\NDid anyone contact you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.91,0:43:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要帶我去哪\NWhere are you taking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.05,0:43:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回答我的問題\NAnswer my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.42,0:43:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒人聯繫我\NNo. Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.69,0:43:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人知道了我們的事\NThere's someone who knows about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.82,0:43:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道你在哪\NWho knows where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.70,0:43:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道我們什麼時候見過面\NAnd when we've met.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.39,0:43:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是不是要傷害我\NAre you gonna hurt me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.61,0:43:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和我說實話就什麼事都不會有\NNothing's going to happen if you tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.32,0:43:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在說實話  沒有任何人聯繫我\NI am. I -- I haven't been contacted by anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.46,0:43:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別再撒謊了  瑞秋\NStop lying, Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.83,0:43:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你讓我幹什麼都行\NI will do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.95,0:43:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求你別傷害我\NPlease, just don't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.92,0:43:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想讓你回答我的問題\NWhat I want is for you to answer my questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.94,0:43:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣我才能幫你\Nso I can help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.99,0:43:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一直以來都在毀掉我的生活\NAll you have ever done is fuck up my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.29,0:43:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你毀了團契的事\NYou fucked up the fellowship.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.20,0:43:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你毀了我和麗薩的感情\NYou fucked up what I had with Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.66,0:43:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使我都按你說的做了\NEven when I did what you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.96,0:43:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你每次來找我都像變態一樣\NAnd your sick fucking visits,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.57,0:43:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要我哄小孩似的給你讀書\Nand reading to you like a fucking child.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.62,0:43:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有什麼毛病\NWhat is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.08,0:43:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼你就不能放了我\NWhy can't you just leave me be?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.57,0:43:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-為什麼你非要這麼  -住嘴\N- Why do you have to be such a fucking -- - stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.38,0:44:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞秋  別做傻事\NRachel? Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.63,0:44:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞秋\NRachel?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.16,0:44:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會有事的\NEverything's gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.47,0:45:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我做的一切都是想保護你\NAll I've ever done is try to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.42,0:45:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我現在也是想保護你\NThat's what I'm trying to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.32,0:45:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要相信我\NYou have to believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.26,0:45:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我本來沒必要保護你\NI didn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.80,0:45:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那樣事情會簡單得多\NBeen a lot easier if I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.26,0:45:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我還是那樣做了  因為我...\NBut I did. I did it because I --
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.98,0:45:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你幹什麼\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.65,0:45:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昨天我們結束了關於\NYesterday we completed hearings with regard to Articles
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.17,0:46:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彈劾美國總統的聽證會\Nof Impeachment for the president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.18,0:46:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席現在開始聽取委員會動議\NThe chair will now entertain motions from the committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.10,0:46:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生\NMr. Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.16,0:46:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席請阿拉巴馬州議員發言\NThe chair recognizes the congressman from Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.52,0:46:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我建議我們直接開始對提議進行投票\NI move that we put our recommendation directly to a vote
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.29,0:46:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣眾議院435名成員\Nso that debate on this important matter may take place
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.66,0:46:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都可以就此事進行辯論\Non the House floor, open to all 435 members.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.40,0:46:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,委員會有人反對跳過辯論階段嗎\NAre there any objections to bypassing debate in this committee?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.79,0:46:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在開始對是否將彈劾狀\NWe will now vote on recommendation of the Articles
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.90,0:46:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,送交眾議院投票進行表決\Nof Impeachment to the full House.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.28,0:46:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同意提議的請喊"贊成"\NThose in favor of recommendation say, "Aye."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.87,0:46:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.15,0:46:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反對者\NThose opposed?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.17,0:46:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反對\NNay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.73,0:46:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成佔多數\NThe ayes have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.10,0:46:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,委員會正式建議眾議院\NThis committee officially recommends Articles
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.11,0:46:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對彈劾狀進行投票\Nof Impeachment proceed to the House floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.75,0:47:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他來了\NHe's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.59,0:47:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統剛剛到達戴維營\NThe vice president is just arriving now here at Camp David.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.32,0:47:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們預計沃克總統\NWe except President Walker to speak within the hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.36,0:47:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會在一小時內宣佈\Nannouncing his official resignation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.50,0:47:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辭去美國總統的職務\Nas president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.79,0:48:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你怎麼樣  -我還好\N- How are you? - I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.32,0:48:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.71,0:48:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在廚房裏煮了咖啡\NI have coffee in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.02,0:48:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要來點嗎  -不用了\N- Would you like some? - I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.92,0:48:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你馬上就要成為\NWell, you're about to become
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.04,0:48:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自由世界最有權勢的人了\Nthe most powerful man in the free world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.54,0:48:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您沒必要這麼做  先生\NYou don't have to do this, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.04,0:48:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我昨晚和科恩談過了\NI spoke to Kern last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.10,0:48:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不肯讓步\NHe's not gonna back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.59,0:48:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我們就打敗他\NSo we'll beat him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.12,0:48:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  弗蘭克\NNo, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.46,0:48:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的支持率只剩8%了\NMy approvals are at eight percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.55,0:48:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使我不被定罪  我也沒有領導國家的威儀了\NEven if I avoid conviction, I have no mandate to lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.01,0:48:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我還是有尊嚴地下台\NSo better I step aside with some dignity
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.39,0:48:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓國家開始康復\Nso the nation can start to heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.14,0:48:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我永遠無法與您比肩  先生\NI can never fill your shoes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.02,0:48:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在沒有選擇了\NYou don't have a choice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.90,0:49:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的信\NYour letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.22,0:49:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.52,0:49:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們去向大家引見美國第46任總統吧\Nshall we go introduce the 46th president of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.32,0:49:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自即日起\NEffective immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.76,0:49:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我辭去美國總統一職\NI am resigning the presidency of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.60,0:49:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特莉莎和我認為這是最合適的辦法\NTricia and I believe that this is the best course of action,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.05,0:49:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既是為了我們和孩子\Nnot only for us and our children,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.26,0:49:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更是為了這個國家\Nbut for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.60,0:50:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我無法否認  這對我們是不幸的一天\NIt's a sad day for us. I can't deny that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.18,0:50:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但讓我心有慰藉的是\NBut I take solace in this:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.80,0:50:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭克·安德伍德將把美德  經驗\NFrank Underwood will bring virtue, experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.11,0:50:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和勇氣帶入總統辦公室\Nand courage to the Oval Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.12,0:50:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由他擔任我的副總統  是我的榮幸\NI have been blessed to have him as my vice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.26,0:50:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而有他這樣的朋友  更是我的幸運\NBut I'm even more blessed to call him my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.05,0:50:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能夠擔任\NIt has been...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.76,0:50:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統一職  服務國家\Nthe greatest honor of my life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.75,0:50:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我這一生無上的榮耀\Nto serve this country as president.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.81,0:50:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感謝我的家人  白宮的工作人員\NI thank my family, my staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.08,0:50:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及所有那些支持我的人\Nand all of those who have supported me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.47,0:50:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,儘管最近幾個月風波不斷\NDespite the last few months,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.48,0:50:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我對祖國的信仰愈發堅定\Nmy faith in this country has never been stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.27,0:50:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝保佑你們\NGod bless all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.30,0:50:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝保佑美利堅合眾國\NAnd god bless the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.88,0:50:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝您的美言  總統先生\NThank you, Mr. President, for those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.48,0:50:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝您好運  先生\NGood luck to you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.14,0:51:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  請舉起右手  跟我宣誓\NSir, please raise your right hand and repeat after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.08,0:51:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本人  弗蘭西斯·J·安德伍德\NI, Francis J. Underwood...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.83,0:51:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本人  弗蘭西斯·J·安德伍德\NI, Francis J. Underwood...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.34,0:51:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在此莊嚴宣誓\NDo solemnly swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.74,0:51:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在此莊嚴宣誓\NDo solemnly swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.90,0:51:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.12,0:51:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.05,0:51:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,國務卿女士\NMadam Secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.49,0:51:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,內閣其餘成員都在白宮等您\NThe rest of the Cabinet is awaiting you at the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.01,0:51:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們希望馬上為您做國家安全簡報  長官\NWe'd like to give you a national security briefing right away, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.50,0:51:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詳情我都知道\NI'm aware of the particulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.50,0:51:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請聯繫一下北京\NCan you please get Beijing on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.52,0:51:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,錢主席已經兩天沒回過總統的電話了\NQian hasn't returned the President's calls for two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.53,0:51:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在總統換人了\NWell, there's a new president now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.93,0:51:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬上給他打電話\NPlease get him on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.62,0:51:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩個小時前  作為三軍統帥\NTwo hours ago, President Underwood,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.61,0:51:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安德伍德總統下達了第一道命令\Nin his first act as commander in chief,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.08,0:51:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要求第七艦隊撤出日本周邊海域\Ngave orders to the seventh fleet to vacate Japanese waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.48,0:51:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這得益於總統與錢主席進行的一次\NThis was a result of a productive conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.09,0:51:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,頗有成效的對話\Nwith President Qian,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.29,0:51:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而錢主席也對該海域的\Nwho gave similar orders
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.42,0:52:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國艦隊下達了撤退的命令\Nto Chinese naval vessels in the same region.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.98,0:52:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他行動挺快啊\NHe moves quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.82,0:52:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是說對中國人  還是對沃克\NDo you mean with the Chinese or with Walker?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.23,0:52:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-馮先生  -怎麼了\N- Mr. Feng? - What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.03,0:52:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們是司法部的  請隨我們走一趟\NU.S. Justice Department. We need you to come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.32,0:52:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-去哪  -你將被遣返回中國\N- Where? - You're going back to China.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.19,0:52:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我申請了政治避難\NI have asylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.50,0:52:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  先生  你的避難請求已經被駁回了\NNo, sir, you don't. Your asylum has been rescinded.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.33,0:52:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有書面證明  無條件無限期的庇護\NI have it in writing. Unconditional and permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.57,0:52:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  我說過了  對你的庇護已經作廢了\NSir, I'm telling you, your asylum has been rescinded.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.66,0:52:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請收拾個人物品  跟我們走\NNow, please, gather your things and come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.78,0:52:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,駁回他的避難不是沒有後果的\NRevoking his asylum will have consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.61,0:52:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是法律上沒問題吧\NBut we're solid from a legal perspective?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.45,0:52:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法律上沒問題  他的文件還沒進入批准流程\NLegally yes. His initial paperwork hasn't been processed,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.29,0:52:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們可以聲稱他對我國利益構成威脅\Nand we can claim he poses a threat to our national interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.61,0:52:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但這會削弱國務院的信譽\NBut it diminishes the integrity of our State Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.30,0:52:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪一個更重要  凱茜  信譽還是和平\NWhat's more important, Cathy? Integrity or peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.40,0:52:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道他會被處決的\NYou know they'll execute him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.20,0:52:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國人說對了一件事\NThe Chinese are right about one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.17,0:53:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有時候  就得捨棄一人  保證全局\NSometimes you have to sacrifice the one for the many.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.53,0:53:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們回華盛頓吧\NLet's get back to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.17,0:53:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  請及時通知我  非常感謝\NOkay. Please let me know. Thanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.93,0:53:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有消息嗎  -還是沒有\N- Anything? - Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.41,0:53:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看看能不能通過戒酒互助會查到他的行蹤\NSee if you can track down anyone from his regular AA meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.89,0:53:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和輔導員談過了\NI spoke to the moderator.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.76,0:53:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說已經有好幾周沒見過道格了\NHe said he hasn't seen Doug in several weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.97,0:53:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我查過醫院  問過他的房東\NI checked all the hospitals, his landlord...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.36,0:53:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  人都到齊了\NSir, everyone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.07,0:53:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  等手頭事一過\NAll right, when this is all over
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.33,0:53:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和南茜一起找道格\NI want you to work with Nancy on finding Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.06,0:53:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經和特區警察局打過招呼\NI've already alerted the D.C. Metro.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.94,0:53:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們會對他的車牌發佈全境通告\NThey put out an APB on his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.19,0:53:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們會找到他的  先生\NWe'll find him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.46,0:53:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克萊爾呢\NClaire?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.22,0:53:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在外面\NJust outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.44,0:53:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咱們走  南茜\NLet's go, Nancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.95,0:53:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士們先生們\NLadies and gentleman,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.67,0:53:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有請總統先生和第一夫人\Nthe President and the first lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.30,0:54:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭西斯\NFrancis,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.86,0:54:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道離你生日還有段時間\NI know your birthday isn't for a couple weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.69,0:54:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我要送你一份禮物\Nbut I got you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.79,0:54:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-這是幹什麼  -打開嘛\N- What's this? - Open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.55,0:54:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我讓人新做了一個\NI had a new one made.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.61,0:55:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我愛你\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.14,0:55:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也愛你\NI love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.67,0:55:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你進去吧\NYou go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.24,0:55:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一起來吧\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.70,0:55:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是我們共同努力的結果\NWe earned this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.45,0:55:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先自己去  好好享受一下\NTake a few moments for yourself first.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.79,0:55:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就在外面\NI'll be out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.83,0:57:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}1789年4月21日  美國第一任副總統約翰·亞當斯在紐約宣誓就職時\N當選總統喬治·華盛頓還在趕往臨時首都的路上\N直到4月30日才正式就任  所以在30日之前的9天裏\N亞當斯作為副總統就成了這個年輕國家的最高行政長官\N美國是先有有副總統  後有總統的\N美國歷史上  曾有9位副總統因總統亡故或辭職而接任成為總統\N1973年  美國副總統阿格紐因貪腐被調查而被迫辭職\N來自密西根州的眾議員福特被時任總統的尼克松任命為副總統\N次年  尼克松因水門事件被迫辭職  福特成為美國第38任總統\N福特未經民主選舉就擔任過副總統和總統的職位
